President Biden has announced his intention to appoint a diverse group of industry and government leaders to the President's National Infrastructure Advisory Council (NIAC). The NIAC advises the White House on reducing physical and cyber risks and improving the security and resilience of the nation's critical infrastructure sectors. The individuals appointed come from a wide range of sectors, including banking and finance, transportation, energy, water, defense, healthcare, and higher education. The appointees have extensive experience and expertise in their respective fields. Some notable appointees include Abedayo Ogunlesi, Chairman and CEO of Global Infrastructure Partners, Maria Lehman, Vice President of Infrastructure at GHD, and Alan Armstrong, President and CEO of Williams.